description: Krazy & Ignatz 1933-1934: "Necromancy by the Blue Bean Bush" is the fifth in a series reprinting George Herriman's early 20th Century comic strip masterpiece. Most of these strips have not seen print since originally running in Hearst newspapers over 70 years ago. Each volume is edited by the San Francisco Cartoon Art Museum's Bill Blackbeard. Krazy & Ignatz 1933-1934 is a hot-baked brickbat of a volume, adance with nearly two full years of the Sunday Krazy Kat (Herriman did not use color until 1935), snug between multiple pages of Herriman extras, not the least of which include an introduction by Blackbeard, a new "DeBaffler" page, and a stunning layout front and back and throughout by the inimitable Chris Ware!

volume.name: Krazy & Ignatz in "Necromancy by the Blue Bean Bush", The Komplete Kat Komics 1933-1934

description: The outlaw lawman Rio encounters a young lad with incredibly good luck at cards but some mighty bad luck in life. Dark Horse Comics is proud to present a classic western tale from master storyteller Doug Wildey in this stunning collection of last year's two-issue series. Collected for the first time ever, readers can join our hero as he rides shotgun on a stagecoach to San Francisco's Barbary Coast, where he encounters a strange game of poker and even stranger poker partners! Lovingly rendered by this legendary artist, each painted color page brings the old West to life with a lush and lavish realism. This volume also includes a ten-page section of never-before-published art from Wildey's long and varied career as an illustrator in a myriad of fields. As an extra bonus, the collection's cover logo is embossed with special silver foil stamp.

name: The Wild Man of the Jungles!

description: Areala has been assigned to intensive training under the personal supervision of Cardinal Stark, but she soon finds that far more is at stake than a mere training course. Stark is out to shut down the Order of Warrior Nuns, and intends to use her performance to convince his superiors to do exactly that. A single misstep could mean the end of everything she's fought for! Meanwhile, an elite convocation of Magic Priests must get to the bottom of eerie phenomena in Libya. Do these strange goings-on require direct intervention by the Vatican... and if so, will the Warrior Nun Order still exist to deal with them? ¬†

name: Hands Of Fate, Fists Of Fury

description: While Areala contemplates the revelations made to her by Cardinal Stark, madness threatens to engulf the Arab world. Inexplicably enticed by Az Rabah's charisma and the fanatical preaching of Hafidh Aziz, even moderate Arab nations rally to his cause and become subservient to his will. In an effort to save the world from the ultimate evil that is Az Rabah, the Vatican launches an all-out attack on his headquarters in Libya. As a member of the Vatican's strike force, Areala believes that she has an opportunity to demonstrate to her superiors that the Warrior Nuns are still a viable defense force.

Father Clifton completes his tale of the Crimson Nun's crusade to protect the world from the forces of evil. In his story, the Crimson Nun learns that Adolf Hitler himself is behind the mission to find Azazel's prison-tomb. In order to prevent Hitler from gaining access to the power and knowledge rumored to be offered by the imprisoned angel, she must battle not only her archenemy Mordecai Black, but elements of the German Kriegsmarine and Hitler's elite bodyguard, the Liebstandarte. When Father Clifton's tale is done, Areala learns that, once again, an agent of evil seeks the tomb of Azazel. ¬†

Deep in the Israeli desert, Areala fights her fiercest battle yet! Locked in mortal combat with the relentless Mr. Zhu, Areala must draw upon all of her experience and training to defeat this implacable foe. Death waits for the first wrong step as these two warriors duel atop the treacherous mountain peaks of Dudael. Will Areala be able to triumph over Mr. Zhu and stop Ruprecht Marsch before he locates Azazel and gains the power he needs to implement his evil plans? ¬†

Evil forces have gathered in secret within the corridors of the Vatican itself in an attempt to destroy the two most powerful arms of the Church's defense, the Magic Priests and the Warrior Nuns. Ancient enemies of these two orders have allied themselves in order to crush them and satisfy the lust for revenge that has consumed their dark souls for centuries. Fortunately for the Church, Areala is aware of this sinister plot and rushes to the Vatican to try and save everything she holds sacred from annihilation. Will she arrive in time, and will she survive the wrath of this dark alliance? ¬†
